<paragraph id="8BF336F1BB7FFFFAFF01EDB2FAE3FF77" blockId="5.[151,1437,152,603]" box="[198,1385,152,178]" pageId="5" pageNumber="557">
Male terminalia (
<figureCitation id="13772A74BB7FFFFAFE56EDB2FE6CFF77" box="[401,486,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="5.[151,270,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,661,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-208@5.[151,1436,661,1876]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Melanophora spp. 9–10. Wing of Melanophora chia sp. nov. 9. ♂, holotype. 10. ♀, paratype. 11–12. Epandrial complex in posterior view. 11. Melanophora chia sp. nov. (♂, paratype), scale bar: 0.1 mm. 12. Melanophora roralis (Linnaeus) (♂, Sardinia), scale bar: 0.2 mm." pageId="5" pageNumber="557">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Cerci, in posterior view, very narrow; basally not or very slightly enlarged.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF336F1BB7FFFFAFF01ED94FDF6FF1D" blockId="5.[151,1437,152,603]" box="[198,636,190,216]" pageId="5" pageNumber="557">
<emphasis id="B938EAE3BB7FFFFAFF01ED94FEABFF1D" bold="true" box="[198,289,190,216]" pageId="5" pageNumber="557">Female</emphasis>
differs from male as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF336F1BB7FFFFAFF01EDCFFE4CFF3A" blockId="5.[151,1437,152,603]" box="[198,454,229,255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="557">
Body length. 
<quantity id="4CB49B14BB7FFFFAFEA2EDCFFE48FF3A" box="[357,450,229,255]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="557" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF336F1BB7FFFFAFF01EC26FF64FDF1" blockId="5.[151,1437,152,603]" pageId="5" pageNumber="557">Colour. Frontal vitta light brown; gena, lower part of parafacial and occipital region yellow; vibrissal angle, dorsal half of parafacial, fronto-orbital plate, vertex, antenna, palpus and prementum black. Pleural sclerites, notopleuron, postpronotal lobes, as well as a wide medial vitta on scutum yellow; scutum, between dorsocentral and intra-alar rows black to dark brown; scutellum entirely black. Legs with coxa and trochanter orange-yellow and tibia, femur and tarsus black. Halter with black knob and orange-yellow stem. Lower calypter only slightly infuscated and upper calypter hyaline. Wing infuscated but with a whitish spot at the tip. Abdomen entirely black, except for anterior half of syntergite 1+2 and sides of tergite 3 that are brownishorange.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF336F1BB7FFFFAFF01EF6BFE16FD9E" blockId="5.[151,1437,152,603]" box="[198,412,577,603]" pageId="5" pageNumber="557">Head. Arista bare.</paragraph>
